 with tragic stories of lost manuscripts and persecuted writers, there is ample evidence of an unbroken thread of political discourse through art. The book concludes with a consideration of the impact of two centuries of dangerous texts on post-Soviet Russia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aLittérature russexThèmes, motifsx20e siècle. 0aNationalism in literature. 0aNationalisme et littératurexHistoirex20e sièclexRussie. 0aNationalisme et littératurexHistoirex20e sièclexURSSxRussiaxSoviet Union. 0aPolitics and literaturexRussia. 0aPolitics and literaturexSoviet Union. 0aPolitics and literaturezRussia. 0aPolitics and literaturezSoviet Union. 0aPolitics in literature. 0aPolitique et littératurexHistoirex20e sièclexRussie. 0aPolitique et littératurexHistoirex20e sièclexURSS. 0aRussian literaturexPolitical aspects. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300138221423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300138221.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles